%U A396040 93,105,99,97,94,93,95,94,96,95,96,100,107,110
%N A396040 Minimum k such that k^10 can be expressed as the sum of n distinct positive 10th powers.
%H A396040 Zhao hui Du, <a href="https://bbs.emath.ac.cn/forum.php?mod=redirectgoto=findpost&amp;ptid=50186&amp;pid=138845&amp;fromuid=46">10th power calculation</a>.
%H A396040 Jean-Charles Meyrignac, <a href="http://euler.free.fr">Computing Minimal Equal Sums of Like Powers</a>.
%H A396040 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/DiophantineEquation10thPowers.html">Diophantine Equation--10th Powers</a>.
%e A396040 a(14) = 172 because 172^10 = 157^10 + 151^10 + 141^10 + 133^10 + 129^10 + 126^10 + 110^10 + 83^10 + 68^10 + 44^10 + 37^10 + 32^10 + 31^10 + 12^10 and no integer smaller than 172 can be expressed as the sum of 14 distinct positive 10th powers.
